ve latest-user previews can surface internal provider events such as\n   subagent notifications. Those records should remain available in `records`,\n   but `sessions` and `timeline` previews should either label or skip them.\n - Observed branch/review/change targets show relation evidence, not ownership.\n   A branch can be observed by background review or sidecar work.\n \n This means the minimal tools are feasible without a storage rewrite, but the\n read layer should be careful: sort by recency, expose match evidence, keep\n timeline light, and page records by turn-local position.\n+\n+### Storage Decision\n+\n+Do not add persisted lightweight timeline data yet.\n+\n+The current storage is good enough for the first handoff tools:\n+\n+- `TurnSummary` gives ordered turns and capture metadata.\n+- `TurnDetail.records` gives authoritative per-turn render order.\n+- the session transcript list gives full records by hash.\n+- environment snapshots give observed branch/review/change evidence.\n+\n+The important distinction is storage shape versus command output. It is fine for\n+the read layer to scan or hydrate existing records internally, as long as the\n+agent-facing `timeline` response remains compact. The transcript itself should\n+be returned only by `records`, and `records` should be bounded by default.\n+\n+Revisit storage only if real usage shows a concrete bottleneck, such as very\n+large sessions making repeated timeline reads too slow, or if providers expose\n+reliable parent/root session fields that would let us store session lineage\n+without guessing.\n \n ## Design Bias\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:55:43.011Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}